&gt; system) I think it has to do simply with the people. I had a lot 
&gt; of fun authoring some of the story line in the Sundering. 
&gt; (Ghuratan and Dhuratan and the begotten). I did so mostly on the 
&gt; fly, and PvP could have only enhaced that, however I don’t think 
&gt; it would have went as smooth as it did on the Non-PvP server. 
&gt; When it comes down to the PvP server, you’ll probably find 
&gt; people less concerned about role playing and more concerned 
&gt; about owning their fellow man. If we don’t get past this, 
&gt; everyone who really thirsts for Roleplay with either stay away 
&gt; or leave. 

&gt; Everyone take responsibility for your actions and the actions of 
&gt; your friends. We are the only ones that can ensure the 
&gt; successful life of the PvP server and have fun doing it. There 
&gt; is a perfect balance out there somewhere, I don’t know if we’ll 
&gt; ever find that “perfect balance” but, I think we can come close. 
&gt; As much as I like going on the Dark Elf hunts, its not enough 
&gt; and should be only a fraction of what we look to for fun. We 
&gt; need wars, drama, story lines and roleplaying, not just killing. 
&gt; We need to kill in role rather than just in race. If you’re a 
&gt; Human with Dark Elf friends and you want to hang with your 
&gt; buddies (which doesn’t seem quite right in role) come up with a 
&gt; story line that supports your alliance. We need to figure out 
&gt; viable fixes to the problems of Lvl and Loot. 

&gt; Its up to us. 

&gt; Geiger the Warbringer 

&gt; (I may have jumped around a bit as I typed this in portions over 
&gt; a period of time) 
